This directory contains libraries and demos of interface between Java
and Amos II.

---------------
A. Demonstration of Java callout interface from Amos II to Java:

The following three Java source code files demonstrate how Amos II 
foreign functions can be defined in Java:

EvalTest.java
Foreign.java
LenTest.java

To dymamically load and define the foreign functions in the above files
do: 

A1: You first need to download the Java virtual machine from
    http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/index.html

A2: Set PATH to include the directory 'bin' under the JDK

A3: Set CLASSPATH=.;../bin/javaamos.jar
    Set PATH=%PATH%;../bin

A4: javac LenTest.java EvalTest.java Foreign.java

A5: javaamos ..\bin\amos2.dmp

A6: < 'javademo.osql';

Now the above Java programs are loaded into Amos II. To test them, see
instructions in javademo.osql.

---------------
B. Example of callin interface from Java to Amos II.

B1: javac AmosDemo.java

B2: java AmosDemo ..\bin\amos2.dmp



